Desc: A medium port on the border of New Sophiasburgh, widely known as "the Old Port." It has become silent along with countless abandoned cargo ships after the breakdown at the Green-Vanostok line.
An area between the ice sea and the snowfield. Covered with thin ice, the area is inaccessible without the help of the forest guards and vehicles.
A forest area near the ice sea. Although with low Punishing concentration, the thin ice on the ground makes it impossible for animals to thrive and become a stable source of food.
The eastern part of the Old Port with deep waters and huge waves. Machine bio-narwhals are often seen in this area.
A flat snowfield area with fewer Corrupted. The soft soil here makes it a perfect location for camping and agriculture in the initial stage of development.
The largest snow forest near New Sophiasburgh is home to many surviving polar creatures. Navigate with caution to avoid entering the area of fierce beasts by accident.

A group of ruins in the outer area of the city. Once a prosperous industrial town in the old times, the area was gradually abandoned along with the breakout of the Punishing Virus and developed into a lair of the Corrupted.
An area in southern New Sophiasburgh. The energy center is also located here, providing all necessary energy for the entire city, and is the real-deal heart of the urban lifeline.
A medium port on the border of New Sophiasburgh, widely known as "the Old Port." It has become silent along with countless abandoned cargo ships after the breakdown at the Green-Vanostok line.
A flat snowfield area with fewer Corrupted. The soft soil here makes it a perfect location for camping and agriculture in the initial stage of development.
A small inland lake next to the snow forest. The ice lake has been frozen for years. You can occasionally see fish going under the thick ice when walking on the ice.
A group of ruins at the foot of the snow mountain. It was an outpost of an industrial town in the old times. You can probably find some usable supplies here if you search carefully.
A medium port on the border of New Sophiasburgh, widely known as "the Old Port." It has become silent along with countless abandoned cargo ships after the breakdown at the Green-Vanostok line.
An area between the ice sea and the snowfield. Covered with thin ice, the area is inaccessible without the help of the forest guards and vehicles.
An eastern border area with fewer plants than the central area. However, this has made it an ideal shelter for medium and small animals. Traces of snow hare and caribou activities can be found here.
A group of ruins in the outer area of the city. Under the ground here is a web of abandoned mine tunnels of the old times. You can still recycle some remaining mineral resources from there.
In western New Sophiasburgh, there's a tall lighthouse on the top of the mountain from which one can observe the entire sea. The forest guards take turns to stay here to look out for narwhals.
The western area of the Old Port. It has fewer undercurrents and a calmer sea and was therefore selected as the port for "Moses class" icebreakers.
A northern area on the snowfield at the foot of the snow mountain. This high-rising natural barrier has blocked most snow and wind from coming in and kept the temperature stable.
A border area in the northern snow forest. The high terrain and low concentration of Corrupted and bio-animals here make it one of the few areas suitable for human activity.
Ruins near the ice lake. Most of the buildings there were seriously eroded by the snowstorm and are no longer suitable for human habitation, making them perfect residences for many bio-animals.
Located in eastern New Sophiasburgh with a giant whale skeleton in the snowfield of the suburb. It was preserved because the whale has a special meaning for the polar region residents.
